message_content:
As an ocean climate graduate student focusing on the dynamic evolution of coastal systems and their responses to regional climate change, I am applying for multi-source remote sensing and geospatial data from HDX platform for the following purposes:

​DEM Data: To construct high-precision terrain models and analyze spatial correlations between coastal landform evolution and sea-level rise;
​Hydrological/Geological/Soil Data: To investigate groundwater distribution, karst development, and surface sediment properties for coastal stability assessment;
​Continental Shelf Data: To integrate with marine geological data to explore the regulatory role of seabed topography on tidal-wave energy.
The acquired datasets will be integrated into multiscale coupled models to support coastal disaster risk assessment, ecological redline delineation, and blue economy development in Dili. I commit to complying with HDX data use policies and will share research outcomes openly with the academic community. Thank you for your support!

